    "trigger.substring.button-name.middle" : {
      "comment" : "Note: These trigger.substring.button-name.[...] strings are inserted into the other trigger.substring.[...] strings at the format specifiers (%@). Make sure that the combined strings are grammatically correct.\n\nNote 2:\nUse *markdown emphasis* to mark the part of a trigger.substring.button-name.[...] string that matches the corresponding trigger.y.group-row.button-name.[...] string.\nFor most languages, this is the entire string.       E.g. English:   `*Middle Button*`         (Where the corresponding group-row string is: `Middle Button`)\nFor some languages, it's only a part of the string.  E.g. French:    `du *bouton central*`     (Where the corresponding group-row string is: `bouton central`)\nReason: The marked parts will be grayed-out. This helps the visual scannability of the UI.     (Bit hard to explain without seeing the UI.)",
